about.summary: CMake is an extensible, open-source system that manages the build process

name: cmake
raw_recipe:
package:
  name: cmake
  version: 3.5.0

source:
  url: https://cmake.org/files/v3.5/cmake-3.5.0.tar.gz                      # [not win]
  fn: cmake-3.5.0.tar.gz                                                    # [not win]
  sha256: 92c83ad8a4fd6224cf6319a60b399854f55b38ebe9d297c942408b792b1a9efa  # [not win]

  url: https://cmake.org/files/v3.5/cmake-3.5.0-win32-x86.zip               # [win]
  fn: cmake-3.5.0-win32-x86.zip                                             # [win]
  sha256: 807f96230c889b10f2957a47585426af4cdb116a8a77f1caecca83b7d7ab862b  # [win]

build:
  number: 5
  detect_binary_files_with_prefix: true

requirements:        # [unix]
  build:             # [unix]
    - toolchain      # [unix]
    - bzip2 1.0.*    # [unix]
    - curl           # [unix]
    - expat          # [unix]
    - jsoncpp        # [unix]
    - libarchive     # [unix]
    - ncurses 5.9*   # [unix]
    - xz 5.2.*       # [unix]
    - zlib 1.2.*     # [unix]

  run:               # [unix]
    - bzip2 1.0.*    # [unix]
    - curl           # [unix]
    - expat          # [unix]
    - jsoncpp        # [unix]
    - libarchive     # [unix]
    - ncurses 5.9*   # [unix]
    - xz 5.2.*       # [unix]
    - zlib 1.2.*     # [unix]

test:
  files:
    - SSLTest.cmake
  commands:
    - cmake --version
    - cmake -V -P SSLTest.cmake

about:
  home: http://www.cmake.org/
  license: BSD 3-clause
  license_family: BSD
  summary: CMake is an extensible, open-source system that manages the build process

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - blowekamp
    - groutr
    - jakirkham
    - ocefpaf
    - msarahan
